          "body": "Matthew 24-25 is one discourse, delivered Tuesday of Passion Week from the Mount of Olives in answer to the disciples' question about the sign of Christ's coming and the end of the age (24:3). Chapter 24 supplies the prophetic outline; chapter 25 supplies the pastoral exhortation. Three units — virgins (1-13), talents (14-30), sheep and goats (31-46) — share one premise: **the Master is away, He is returning, and the interval is a test.** The chapter ends (25:46) and immediately the Passion begins (26:1-2). The last sustained teaching of Jesus this side of the cross is about His own return in glory."
